cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses training an RL agent using low precision policy distillation, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): RL is a subfield of AI, and the paper discusses using RL to play ATARI games. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper mentions using neuromorphic hardware, which is related to neural computing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper converts a sequence of game frames into discrete actions, which involves computer vision techniques. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses real-time end-to-end game playing, which is relevant to robotics applications.
